description:
&lt;p&gt;We are excited to announce an open position within the Practice Unbound team, which is a commercial business within Here, delivering learning programmes to Primary Care nationally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this role is to create loyal, repeat customers to aid the expansion of the business. The role holder will support the team to deliver outstanding customer service, providing insights into product upgrades, increasing customer lifetime value and upselling and cross selling. They will work with the leadership team to develop retention and expansion strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As someone who works directly with customers, the role holder will be responsible for advocating customer and user needs. They will need to have an in-depth understanding of customer likes and dislikes about our products, which will be discovered through the collection and analysis of qualitative and quantitative data and speaking to customers directly on a regular basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role holder will be the voice of our customers and will be connected with all areas of the business across sales, delivery, product development and marketing to ensure we are moving our products and processes in the right direction for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next Steps&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 6th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact for any questions Lesley.jay@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this role, please apply by submitting an application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here are committed to equality and valuing diversity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
